2. 

In these Regulations— 

“Act of 1968” means Road Traffic Act 1968 (No. 25 of 1968); 

“Act of 1994” means Road Traffic Act 1994 (No. 7 of 1994); 

“Act of 2006” means Road Traffic Act 2006 (No. 23 of 2006); 

“Act of 2010” means Road Traffic Act 2010 (No. 25 of 2010); 

“electric scooter” has the meaning assigned to it in Regulation 2 of the Road 
Traffic (Electric Scooters) Regulations 2024 (S. I No. 199 of 2024); 

“No. 2 Act of 2011” means Road Traffic (No. 2) Act 2011 (No. 28 of 2011); 

“Principal Act” means Road Traffic Act 1961 (No. 24 of 1961); 

“Regulations of 1997” means Road Traffic (Traffic and Parking) Regulations 
1997 (S.I. No. 182 of 1997); 

“Regulations of 2012” means Road Traffic (Traffic and Parking (Amendment) 
(No. 2) Regulations 2012) (S.I. No. 332 of 2012); 

“Regulations of 2024” means the Road Traffic (Traffic and Parking) 
(Amendment) Regulations 2024 (S.I. No. 222 of 2024).
